<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 06 at 2:23AM CDT  by NWS Bismarck</headline>
<description>...STRONG THUNDERSTORMS WILL IMPACT PORTIONS OF NORTHWESTERN BURKE,
NORTH CENTRAL WILLIAMS AND EASTERN DIVIDE COUNTIES THROUGH 300 AM
CDT...
At 223 AM CDT, strong thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 4 miles north of Noonan to 9 miles south of Crosby to
9 miles northwest of Alamo. Movement was east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts to 40 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Noonan around 230 AM CDT.
Other locations in the path of these storms include Columbus and
Wildrose.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
